Add a type-filter dropdown to the Execute Action review dialog. Three options ("All decisions", "Delete only", "Remove from list only") narrow the tree, summary, warning banner, and Execute commit scope — mirroring the "visible = committed" contract established by #410 / #485. A new banner line surfaces hidden delete decisions when the filter is set to a non-delete view, so switching to "Remove only" while pending deletes exist no longer visually clears the destructive-state warning (#502).
